The article announces several nominations and appointments for various positions. Christopher T. Hanson of Michigan has been nominated to be a Member of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. He has extensive experience in nuclear energy, fuel cycle, security, and radioactive waste issues. Kenneth J. Braithwaite of Pennsylvania has been nominated to be the Secretary of the Navy. Braithwaite is a distinguished veteran of the United States Navy and currently serves as Ambassador to the Kingdom of Norway. Kendel S. Ehrlich of Maryland has been nominated to be the Director of the Office of Sex Offenders, Sentencing, Monitoring, Apprehending, Registering, and Tracking at the Department of Justice.